{
  "texts": [
    "Line Notation (SLN) 14 allows for macro atoms which specify multiple atoms in a substructure.",
    "The Hierarchical Editing Language for Macromolecules (HELM) 15 represents complex biomolecules by declaring monomers and then connecting them in a polymer line notation.",
    "Hakime et al.",
    "introduced the Character Slicing (CS) method in their work on DeepDTA 16.",
    "The fragmentation products in CS do not correspond to traditional fragments."
  ]
}